# Project: ADM S&OP Dashboard

## Product context
- Client: Agua de Madre (ADM)
- Delivery partner: EXL Partners via VirtualCrew Ltd
- Security is a primary requirement; do not route business data through unapproved third-party services
- Approved email for API and credential coordination: info@virtualcrew.co.uk

## Target stack
- Dashboard frontend target: Next.js 15 (App Router)
- TypeScript in strict mode for frontend work
- Tailwind CSS v4
- shadcn/ui for UI primitives
- Recharts for visualisation
- Supabase for storage and analytics data
- Python for deterministic forecasting and data preparation utilities
- n8n for workflow automation
- Anthropic Claude Sonnet 4.6 for recommendation generation

## Design system
- Background: white (#ffffff)
- Primary brand accent: EXL dark blue (#1a2b4a)
- Positive: green
- Negative: red
- Neutral: slate
- Heading font: Lora
- Body and data font: Inter

## Code style
- Prefer simple, typed, composable functions
- Use named exports for frontend components
- Keep components under 150 lines when practical
- Avoid inline styles; use Tailwind classes
- Avoid `any` in TypeScript and untyped dictionaries in Python when a dataclass or typed mapping fits better
- Add comments only when the logic is not immediately obvious

## Dashboard-specific rules
- KPI cards belong at the top of the dashboard
- Every data table must support sorting, filtering, and CSV export
- Charts must include tooltips, legends, and responsive containers
- Monetary values default to GBP unless a different currency is required by the source
- Dates should use UK-style formatting
- Use server-side data fetching where practical for dashboard reads

## Security rules
- Never hardcode tokens or credentials
- Store secrets in environment variables or secure vaults only
- Do not use Gmail or unapproved third-party APIs for data movement
- Client credentials must not be exchanged through personal email, WhatsApp, or chat
